<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c5"><SPAN CLASS="c6">Avoid bias in race coverage</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c5"><SPAN CLASS="c7">SECTION: </SPAN><SPAN CLASS="c2">LETTERS TO EDITOR</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c5"><SPAN CLASS="c7">LENGTH: </SPAN><SPAN CLASS="c2">83 words</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Editor:</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">Please avoid bias in reporting in the George Zimmerman/ Trayvon Martin case by showing current pictures of both. The pictures selected by your newspaper, and the media in general, are a current, stern-looking picture of Zimmerman next to an old picture of a cute, smiling, cherub-like Martin.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">As you know, this will invoke feelings like &quot;how could anyone have an altercation with such a teddy bear?&quot;</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">This appears to be an attempt to bias the news rather than just report it.</SPAN></P>
<P CLASS="c8"><SPAN CLASS="c2">BRYAN RIEGLE<BR>LEBANON<BR>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
<BR><DIV CLASS="c4"><P CLASS="c5"><SPAN CLASS="c7">LOAD-DATE: </SPAN><SPAN CLASS="c2">July 24, 2013</SPAN></P>
</DIV>
